# CloveJS basic example — HTTP requests
#
# A dependency-free alternative to a Postman/Insomnia collection: this plain
# text format is read natively by JetBrains IDEs (Run > HTTP Client) and by
# VS Code's "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client) — no app install, no
# account, no cloud sync. Click "Send Request" above any block, or run them
# top to bottom.
#
# Start the server first: npm run dev -w clovejs-example-basic

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@wsUrl = ws://localhost:3000

### Hello world
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/hello

### List notes (public) — an array return becomes 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notes

### Who am I? — no session yet, so 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me

### Log in as ada (admin). Both tools keep a cookie jar per file, so the
### clove.sid this sets is sent automatically by every request below.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "ada",
  "password": "secret"
}

### Who am I? — now 200, from the session
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me

### Admin-only route — ada is an admin
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/stats

### Fetch the seeded note by id — 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notes/1

### Create a note — 201, returns the created note
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/notes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "From requests.http",
  "body": "Created via the REST Client / HTTP Client"
}

### Delete the seeded note — 204
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/notes/1

### Fetch it again — gone now, so 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notes/1

### Log out
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/logout

### Who am I? — 401 again
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/me

### Log in as grace (not an admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "grace",
  "password": "secret"
}

### Admin-only route as grace — 403 Forbidden
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/stats

### WebSocket echo — JetBrains HTTP Client only (WebStorm/IntelliJ 2023.2+).
### VS Code's REST Client extension has no WebSocket support;
### use `npx wscat -c ws://localhost:3000/ws/echo`
### there instead — see src/ws/echo.ts.
WEBSOCKET {{wsUrl}}/ws/echo

Hello over WebSocket
===
wait-for-server
Sent after the echo comes back
